{% render 'section-new-faq-watch-styles-min' %}
<div class="section-container">
                <h2 class="faq-title hero__overlay-title section-title has-animated">
                    Luxury Watches FAQ
                </h2>
            <div class="new-faq_wrapp">
                <div class="new-faq_item">
                    <div class="new-faq_item-title">
                        <p class="font-title">
                            How much does our watch authentication service cost?
                        </p>
                        <a href="javascript:void(0)"  class="font-title">
                            +
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="new-faq_item-text">
                        <p class="font-description">
                            The price of watch authentication generally falls within the range of $50 to $105, which can vary depending on factors such as the brand and desired turnaround time.
<br><br>
For instance, if you need to authenticate a Rolex watch within a 30-minute timeframe, the cost would be $105. However, if you are able to wait for 12 hours, the fee for authenticating the same watch would be reduced to $50.
<br><br>
Ultimately, the pricing is influenced by the specific time constraints and the brand associated with your watch. It's worth noting that higher-end and prestigious brands tend to command higher authentication costs.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="new-faq_item">
                    <div class="new-faq_item-title">
                        <p class="font-title">
                            How do I authenticate my watch?
                        </p>
                        <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="font-title">
                            +
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="new-faq_item-text">
                        <p class="font-description">
                            You have the option to authenticate your watch on your own. Depending on the brand, production year, and specific model, genuine watches possess unique characteristics that counterfeit ones can never replicate. This is where you need to focus and discern the authenticity of the watch.
<br><br>
You can refer to our specialized guides, which provide detailed instructions on how to authenticate various brands. These guides offer a comprehensive checklist that can help you arrive at a 99% accurate authenticity determination.
<br><br>
However, we highly recommend seeking professional assistance to ensure the best possible outcome. 
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="new-faq_item">
                    <div class="new-faq_item-title">
                        <p class="font-title">
                           How long does it take to get my watch authenticated?
                        </p>
                        <a href="javascript:void(0)" class="font-title">
                            +
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="new-faq_item-text">
                        <p class="font-description">
                            The duration of the authentication process for a watch can vary, ranging from as little as 30 minutes to up to 12 hours. It primarily depends on the amount you are willing to invest to expedite the process.
<br><br>
For instance, if you possess a Rolex watch and desire a 30-minute authentication, the cost would be $105. However, if you opt to wait for 12 hours, the fee reduces to $50.
<br><br>
Therefore, the determining factor here is how much you are willing to allocate financially for the authentication service.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
               
            </div>
  <div class="new-faq_bottom font-title">
      <p>Have more questions? Visit our <a href="https://legitgrails.frontkb.com/en">Help Center</a></p>
  </div>
        </div>

